) female tergite VIII; (
<emphasis id="BDA0EAB85F395215FD8BF98FFD8D1752" bold="true" box="[553,576,1541,1562]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1126">13</emphasis>
) male sternite VIII; (
<emphasis id="BDA0EAB85F395215FCA7F98FFC901752" bold="true" box="[773,861,1541,1562]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1126">14-15, 17</emphasis>
) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (
<emphasis id="BDA0EAB85F395215FEF3F996FEA51779" bold="true" box="[337,360,1564,1585]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1126">16</emphasis>
) apical portion of ventral process of aedeagus. Scale bars: 11: 1.0 mm; 12-15, 17: 0.5 mm; 16: 0.2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DBAB66225F36521AFF10FDF6FBD013E0" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307295" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5307295" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307295/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="1127" startId="8.[178,218,636,658]" targetBox="[190,1078,218,597]" targetPageId="8">
