<emphasis id="BDA0EAB85F36521AFCDCFB67FC3D144A" box="[894,1008,1261,1282]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="1127">T. inexcisus</emphasis>
ASSING
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8F6B36AA5F36521AFF10FA86FBF01407" blockId="8.[178,1086,1129,1515]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1127">
<keyLead id="3425959F5F36521AFF10FA86FBF01407" pageId="8" pageNumber="1127">
- Elytra shorter, approximately 0.75 times as long as pronotum (
<figureCitation id="17EF2A2F5F36521AFCEEFA81FC581469" box="[844,917,1291,1313]" captionStart="Figs 11-17" captionStartId="7.[178,218,1518,1540]" captionTargetBox="[186,1064,212,1488]" captionTargetId="figure-1@7.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 11-17: Tetartopeus korgei nov.sp. (11-16) and paratype of Lathrobium maculatum LAST (17): (11) forebody; (12) female tergite VIII; (13) male sternite VIII; (14-15, 17) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (16) apical portion of ventral process of aedeagus. Scale bars: 11: 1.0 mm; 12-15, 17: 0.5 mm; 16: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307293" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307293/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="1127">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
).: posterior margin of sternite VIII with small or minute median incision; ventral process of aedeagus of different shape.................................................................................................9
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="34202E0F5F36521AFF10FAD3FBF014A2" pageId="8" pageNumber="1127">
<paragraph id="8F6B36AA5F36521AFF10FAD3FBF314D5" blockId="8.[178,1086,1129,1515]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1127">
<keyLead id="3425959F5F36521AFF10FAD3FBF314D5" pageId="8" pageNumber="1127">
9. Head with slightly sparser punctation (
<figureCitation id="17EF2A2F5F36521AFDD1FAD3FD0C1427" box="[627,705,1369,1391]" captionStart="Figs 11-17" captionStartId="7.[178,218,1518,1540]" captionTargetBox="[186,1064,212,1488]" captionTargetId="figure-1@7.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 11-17: Tetartopeus korgei nov.sp. (11-16) and paratype of Lathrobium maculatum LAST (17): (11) forebody; (12) female tergite VIII; (13) male sternite VIII; (14-15, 17) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (16) apical portion of ventral process of aedeagus. Scale bars: 11: 1.0 mm; 12-15, 17: 0.5 mm; 16: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307293" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307293/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="1127">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
).: ventral process of aedeagus apically furcate (with a dorsal and a ventral projection of similar shapes) in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="17EF2A2F5F36521AFEB6FA0DFEB014D5" box="[276,381,1415,1437]" captionStart="Figs 11-17" captionStartId="7.[178,218,1518,1540]" captionTargetBox="[186,1064,212,1488]" captionTargetId="figure-1@7.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 11-17: Tetartopeus korgei nov.sp. (11-16) and paratype of Lathrobium maculatum LAST (17): (11) forebody; (12) female tergite VIII; (13) male sternite VIII; (14-15, 17) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (16) apical portion of ventral process of aedeagus. Scale bars: 11: 1.0 mm; 12-15, 17: 0.5 mm; 16: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307293" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307293/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="1127">Figs 14-16</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry id="F7C3763A5F36521AFE32FA0DFE1714D5" box="[400,474,1415,1437]" name="Turkey" pageId="8" pageNumber="1127">Turkey</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="4D10F8485F36521AFE41FA02FDDD14D5" box="[483,528,1416,1437]" country="Turkey" name="Kars" pageId="8" pageNumber="1127">Kars</collectingRegion>
................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="48D44D295F36521AFC39FA02FC3C14D4" authority="Assing, 2014" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2014" box="[923,1009,1415,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Tetartopeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="1127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="korgei" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis id="BDA0EAB85F36521AFC39FA02FC3C14D4" box="[923,1009,1415,1437]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="1127">T. korgei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A69357C35F36521AFC5AFA02FBF314D5" box="[1016,1086,1416,1437]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1127" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8F6B36AA5F36521AFF10FA2DFBF014A2" blockId="8.[178,1086,1129,1515]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1127">
<keyLead id="3425959F5F36521AFF10FA2DFBF014A2" pageId="8" pageNumber="1127">
- Head with denser punctation.: ventral process of aedeagus with a short tooth-shaped dorsal projection and with a hook-shaped ventral projection (
<bibRefCitation id="EB454B5B5F36521AFC8CFA34FC63149B" author="ASSING V" box="[814,942,1470,1492]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1127" pagination="1063 - 1071" refId="ref6015" refString="ASSING V. (2010): Two new species of Tetartopeus from Turkey (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 42 (2): 1063 - 1071." type="journal article" year="2010">Assing 2010</bibRefCitation>
